China reiterated its "one country, two systems" policy towards Taiwan while introducing an anti-secession law.
The Mainland Affairs Council closely monitors China's communication with the US regarding this law.
Taiwan strongly opposes Beijing's attempt to legalize invasion.
President Chen warned of destabilization if the law passes.
Pro-independence activists urge Taiwan to resist Beijing's coercion.
The US and EU view the law as detrimental to peace.
Taiwan plans to counteract the law through legislative measures.
The Legislative Yuan will voice opposition to China's anti-secession legislation.
China defends the law as a means to prevent Taiwan independence.
